abstract: The police chief in Vermont's largest city used an anonymous Twitter account to troll a government critic, he admitted this week.
snippet: The police chief in Vermont's largest city used an anonymous Twitter account to troll a government critic, he admitted this week.
lead_paragraph: BURLINGTON, Vt. — The police chief in Vermont's largest city used an anonymous Twitter account to troll a government critic, he admitted this week.
headline_main: Police Chief Admits Anonymously Trolling Critic on Twitter
headline_print_headline: Police Chief Admits Anonymously Trolling Critic on Twitter

abstract: Prime Minister Boris Johnson has won the majority he needs to push through Brexit, but he faces another big challenge from Scotland, where the independence-minded Scottish National Party and its leader Nicola Sturgeon have surged to a commanding position. Here is a look at the factors that will make this a vexing issue for Johnson.
snippet: Prime Minister Boris Johnson has won the majority he needs to push through Brexit, but he faces another big challenge from Scotland, where the independence-minded Scottish National Party and its leader Nicola Sturgeon have surged to a commanding p...
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Prime Minister Boris Johnson has won the majority he needs to push through Brexit, but he faces another big challenge from Scotland, where the independence-minded Scottish National Party and its leader Nicola Sturgeon have surged to a commanding position. Here is a look at the factors that will make this a vexing issue for Johnson.
headline_main: Battle Ahead: Scotland Party Leader Vows Independence Push
headline_print_headline: Battle Ahead: Scotland Party Leader Vows Independence Push

abstract: The United Nations General Assembly on Friday overwhelmingly renewed the mandate for a U.N. agency supporting Palestinian refugees for another three years amid misconduct allegations and a cash shortfall triggered by a halt in U.S. funding.
snippet: The United Nations General Assembly on Friday overwhelmingly renewed the mandate for a U.N. agency supporting Palestinian refugees for another three years amid misconduct allegations and a cash shortfall triggered by a halt in U.S. funding.
lead_paragraph: UNITED NATIONS — The United Nations General Assembly on Friday overwhelmingly renewed the mandate for a U.N. agency supporting Palestinian refugees for another three years amid misconduct allegations and a cash shortfall triggered by a halt in U.S. funding.
headline_main: In Face of U.S. Opposition, U.N. Renews Agency Helping Palestinian Refugees
headline_print_headline: In Face of U.S. Opposition, U.N. Renews Agency Helping Palestinian Refugees

abstract: In several new and recent specials, Seth Meyers, Tiffany Haddish and others largely ignore politics in favor of the personal or just plain silly.
snippet: In several new and recent specials, Seth Meyers, Tiffany Haddish and others largely ignore politics in favor of the personal or just plain silly.
lead_paragraph: In Taylor Mac’s “Gary,” the most ambitious comedy to open on Broadway in years, the title character is a clown who badly wants to upgrade to a fool. What’s the difference? A clown seeks laughs, but a fool also aims to save the world.
